About the job

Engineering Manager

Position Summary

This position will report to our Vice President of Manufacturing and will be an integral part of the business development for Bellmont. This is a unique opportunity within a high growth manufacturing company to manage numerous crucial company improvement projects and people. Strategic thinking and strong leadership will be key in the success of this role.

Key Responsibilities

  • Assign tasks/projects to direct reports
  • Project Management
  • Identify key projects for company improvement.
  • Provide metrics to the project improvements.
  • Equipment Procurement
  • 5S and Kaizen events and coaching.
  • Reduce company annual spend and/or increase company profitability.
  • Foster a culture of safety, continuous improvement, quality, and FUN.

Attributes / Qualifications

  • A four-year degree in Engineering or a related field.
  • Certified Six Sigma preferred
  • Strong communication/relationship skills with the ability to connect with all levels of the organization.
  • Ability to thrive in an environment of uncertainty.
  • High Level competency in Microsoft Office products.
  • Strong analytics.
  • Ability to work in a fast-paced high growth environment.
  • AutoCAD proficient.
  • Understanding of Lean / JIT / TOC / TQM.

This job description is not intended to be an exhaustive list of all duties or responsibilities associated with the job. Other job-related duties may be assigned.
